        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Try to remove that autocmd it's not required.\nUse termguicolors in combination with guicursor.\n```lua\nvim.opt.termguicolors = true\nvim.opt.guicursor = \"a:hor100-blinkwait0-blinkon50-blinkoff5000\"\n```\nI think it's not required to set a custom $PROMPT_COMMAND like said in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/37917\nIf your set a custom $PROMPT_COMMAND, ensure that you append not overwrite\n```bash\n# My custom\necho $PROMPT_COMMAND\n__systemd_osc_context_precmdline;tmux_rename_window\n\n\n# example in .bashrc, tmux_rename_window == custom function\nif [ -n \"${PROMPT_COMMAND}\" ]; then\n\tPROMPT_COMMAND=\"${PROMPT_COMMAND};tmux_rename_window\"\nelse\n\tPROMPT_COMMAND=\"tmux_rename_window\"\nfi\n\n```",
