        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> vim.opt.termguicolors = true\n> vim.opt.guicursor = \"a:hor100-blinkwait0-blinkon50-blinkoff5000\"\n\nthis breaks block (and other shape changes) cursor inside neovim itself (during work session)\n\n\nAnd, talking about prompt/pre/post commands (I'm using `zsh`, and not `bash`, so there is a bit another syntax for that) - I'd like to avoid \"restoring\" cursor shape that way, as it breaks the possibility to temporary change it by sending esc-sequence with echo (because that prompt/pre/post command will execute after echo again).\n\nAnd I'd also like to avoid making nvim an alias to `nvim; echo \"${fix_shape}\"` as it was also suggested in corresponding issues.\n\nActually, for now it works fine with `vim.cmd([[set guicursor= | call nvim_ui_send(\"\\033[0 q\")]])` in autocommand.\nIt is just my internal perfectionist wants to make that lua-api way (which doesn't work somewhy).\nAnd I guess I'd stay with `cmd`-way until I find a way to make lua api to work.\n",
