        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk It seems like not a quite.\n\nWell, actually, the issue from initial message - looks corellating to the mentioned issue,\nbut as for now (at the time of my previous comment) I found that \"unsetting guicursor\" + \"sending `\\e[0 q`\" **works** when paired,\nbut only when they called at vimscript.\n```lua\nvim.cmd[[set guicursor= | call nvim_ui_send(\"\\033[0 q\")]]\n```\n\nAnd doing analogous thing in lua doesn't work: \n```lua\nvim.o.guicursor = \"\" -- and even `nil`\nvim.api.nvim_ui_send(\"\\033[0 q\")\n```\n\nInitially I thought it is because vimscript unsets guicursor in somehow different way, than lua, but no. Even\n```lua\nvim.cmd([[set guicursor=]])\nvim.api.nvim_ui_send(\"\\033[0 q\")\n```\ndoesn't work too.\nIt only works if they called altogether in vimscript.",
