        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "by the way, somewhy that autocmd-hack has just stopped to work today (in every terminal, inside and outside tmux, and no matter in Lua way (thanks @zeertzjq for hint) or \"original\" vimscript one)...\n\nI think the fact that I have updated the system may corellate with that, but neither nvim nor unibillium, nor even ncurses (as terminfos provider in the distro) was updated, so I don't know what can affect that thing then 🤷 \n\n\n// well, most interesting fact, that sending that sequence manually (with `echo`) still works everywhere.\nBut despite setting autogroup even in `nvim --clean`, cursor stopped to restore after exiting today\n\n\nUhm...\n**UPD1**:\nI got this once. Not sure, if related...\n\n<img width=\"790\" height=\"48\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a9616df-47de-441d-a9f9-f0573e9a64bc\" />\n\n\n**UPD2**: after some more investigation:\n\n1) well, now it \"doesn't work\" in the same way as I described in issue starting message:\nsay, in Konsole it doesn't work with `TERM=konsole*`, but do work with `TERM=xterm*` and `TERM=tmux*`, and even `TERM=st`, `TERM=vte`.\nin `xterm` it doesn't work with default `TERM=xterm`, but do work with `konsole` (?!?), `st`, but not with `vte`...\nin `vte` it also doesn't work with default `vte` (?!?), works with `konsole` (?!?!?), works with `st`, and doesn't work with `xterm`\n\n2) in tmux it \"doesn't work\" only in some tabs, and **works fine in others** (?!?!?!?!)\nand I still can't find what's the difference between that tabs...\n\n\n**UPD3**:\n\n3) (!!!!) well, it works in Konsole with `TERM=konsole{,-{256color,direct}}` too, if I run it like this:\n```\n$ (unset KONSOLE_VERSION; nvim)\n```\nSo, it looks like it can be somehow related to Konsole hacks in nvim source code (I remember there was something about looking for `KONSOLE_*` variables and doing some personalized stuff for Konsole)",
